
[1]gesture

   GES'TURE, n. [L. gestus, from gero, to bear, to do.]

   1. A motion of the body or limbs, expressive of sentiment or passion;
   any action or posture intended to express an idea or a passion, or to
   enforce an argument or opinion. It consists chiefly in the actions or
   movements of the hands and face, and should be suited to the subject.

   2. Movement of the body or limbs.

   Grace was in all her steps, heaven in her eye,

   In every gesture dignity and love.

             GES'TURE, v.t. To accompany with gesture or action.
